  <h2>4. Identity verification</h2>
  <p>All developers and clients who engage in paid projects must complete identity verification via <strong>Stripe Identity</strong>. This is a legal requirement to operate our escrow service and comply with applicable anti-money-laundering regulations. We do not store raw identity documents — they are processed and retained by Stripe in accordance with Stripe's privacy policy.</p>

  <h2>5. The Tessera marketplace</h2>
  <p>Tessera provides the platform and tooling; we do not employ developers or act as a staffing agency. Contracts formed through the platform are between the client and the developer directly. Tessera acts as an escrow agent and facilitator, not as a party to any service agreement.</p>
  <p>We reserve the right to review, approve, or reject any developer portfolio or project listing at our sole discretion.</p>

  <h2>6. Payments and escrow</h2>
  <p>All payments made through Tessera are processed by <strong>Stripe, Inc.</strong> and held in a Stripe-managed escrow account. Funds are released to developers only when milestones are approved. We do not commingle client funds with our operating accounts.</p>
  <p>A platform fee is charged on each milestone release. The current fee is disclosed at the time of quote acceptance and reflected in your project dashboard. Fees are non-refundable except where required by applicable law.</p>
  <p>For full details on how escrow works, see our <a href="<%= legal_escrow_policy_path %>">Escrow Policy</a>.</p>

